PN,41702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1777385514
OL,3,CPetrol station owner losing thousands
OL,4,Cevery month to fuel thefts
OL,6,FHe's now installed ANPR cameras to
OL,7,Fflag repeat offenders, but says
OL,8,Fmotorists are still taking advantage.
OL,10,FSpeaking to ITV Meridian he said that
OL,11,Fthere's been a noticeable increase
OL,12,Fsince the start of the Iran war.
OL,14,F"We've definitely seen a big increase
OL,15,Fin drive-offs, and also no means of
OL,16,Fpayment forms that we're receiving
OL,17,Fthrough the door," Ben said.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1777385514
OL,3,CPetrol station owner losing thousands
OL,4,Cevery month to fuel thefts
OL,6,F"I think people have the perception
OL,7,Fthat this is a big oil company,
OL,8,Fwhereas we are actually a small family
OL,9,Fbusiness, and we bought our fuel off
OL,10,Fthe oil company.
OL,12,F"So when we do receive the drive-offs
OL,13,Fand the no means of payment, it's
OL,14,Factually coming out of our accounts
OL,15,Fand not the big boys."
OL,17,FBen says that those drivers who leave
OL,18,Fwithout paying are filling up with
OL,19,Fanything from #20 up to more than
OL,20,F#100, but overall since March, they
OL,21,Fhave lost around #1000 a month.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1777385514
OL,3,CPetrol station owner losing thousands
OL,4,Cevery month to fuel thefts
OL,6,FHe is working closely with police, but
OL,7,Fsays it's difficult to catch every
OL,8,Fdriver who leaves without paying.
OL,10,F"It's super frustrating," he added.
OL,12,F"We've obviously got our training in
OL,13,Fprocess, and we have ANPR cameras to
OL,14,Fstop those repeat offenders.
OL,16,F"You can imagine the amount of cars
OL,17,Fthat come through on our forecourt -
OL,18,Fto try and gauge which one you think
OL,19,Fis going to be a drive-off and not a
OL,20,Fdrive-off, it's near enough impossible.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1777385514
OL,3,CPetrol station owner losing thousands
OL,4,Cevery month to fuel thefts
OL,6,F"But we look for signs and we look for
OL,7,Ftriggers.
OL,9,F"Our staff are well trained on it, but
OL,10,Fthere's no telling which one could be
OL,11,Fa potential drive-off."
OL,13,FA Treasury spokesperson said:
OL,14,F"Motorists are paying more because of
OL,15,Fthe war in Iran. This is not our war
OL,16,Fand that is why we did not join it.
OL,26,@vD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/6
